node.text:
Presented by @Nestseekers📍809 Meadow Lane, Southampton NYL
-
In Southampton's storied waterfront district of Meadow Lane, down a gated drive awaits an enchanting enclave for the ever-discerning connoisseur. Curated by renowned architect Dimitiris Balamotis and constructed by Hamilton Hoge this magnificent traditional residence comprises nearly 6,000 SF of elegantly appointed living space.

Flawless design maximizes natural light and scale via soaring ceilings and complimented by floor-to-ceiling windows and doors. Sited amid a secluded 2 acre +/- parcel overlooking the Shinnecock Bay with 400 SF of bulkheaded waterfront. Defined by its myriad water views, its location allows not only for captivating sunset vistas, but for a sense of privacy and seclusion, an ever rare commodity.

Abundant foliage instills an opulent quality into the property's tiered outdoor grounds, which feature Bayside gunite pool, all-weather tennis court, carriage house with upstairs apartment, private dock for water sports, extensive landscaping and gardens, deeded ocean access via a path on the ocean side of Meadow Lane.
_

node.text:
Inside One Thousand Museum in #Miami
Contact @thedavidsiddonsgroup for more details🙏 

🌟One Thousand Museum is an architectural masterpiece by the late Zaha Hadid and offers only 84 full and half floor residences starting at 4,600 SF. 1000 Museum received 5 stars from Forbes Travel Guide for its services and lifestyle and it is the only residential building in the world to have an exclusive partnership with Forbes Travel Guide. Need we say more? No direct beach access, so if you want an immediate beach experience or service this won’t be for you.  The condo does have a South beach beach club with transportation. Also One Thousand Museum offers a helipad. So if you own a helicopter or frequently use one, this is the Miami luxury condo for you.

🌟Truly functional as a family home.  Each floor plan provides for a lot of natural light; there is light in every single room even within the bathrooms and walk-in closets, which changes the look and feel of the units. The flow of the units is also amazing with large corridors and high ceilings. Furthermore the majority of the columns are on the exterior of the building providing the residents with open, ample living rooms. Nothing feels cramped and all units have a home-like flow and feeling to them. 

📲 For more information contact David Siddons at 305.508.0899
